First Lady Melania Trump attended the dedication ceremony for the REACH, an expansion of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. As Honorary Chair of the Kennedy Center, she delivered opening remarks and expressed her appreciation for the Kennedy Center leadership and donors. The First Lady emphasized the importance of the arts in bringing people together and praised the new addition for its value to Washington D.C. and the nation as a whole. The REACH is set to open to the public on September 7, 2019. The event was closed to the press.